- Yes, it's the happiest
day of my whole life.

811
00:46:39,780 --> 00:46:44,780
Bucky, I love you, I love
you, now my life is perfect.

812
00:46:56,889 --> 00:46:57,969
Daddy.

813
00:46:57,969 --> 00:46:59,753
You'll never leave me, will you?

814
00:46:59,753 --> 00:47:00,761
- Baby, why would I leave you?

815
00:47:00,761 --> 00:47:02,320
I just married you.

816
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:07,120
- It kinda smells in
here like insect spray.

817
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,691
It's cruel.

818
00:47:08,691 --> 00:47:11,010
The way they kill them that
way is cruel, don't you think?

819
00:47:11,010 --> 00:47:12,680
- I'm only thinking of one thing.

820
00:47:12,680 --> 00:47:13,990
- Wait, just let me get my nightgown.

821
00:47:13,990 --> 00:47:14,940
- No, no nightgown.

822
00:47:16,133 --> 00:47:17,333
I been dreaming of this.

823
00:47:18,410 --> 00:47:20,333
Aww jeez, baby, I love you so much.

824
00:47:20,333 --> 00:47:24,213
You're so good, and so
sweet, and so beautiful.

825
00:47:24,213 --> 00:47:26,333
- You do love me, don't you Bucky?

826
00:47:26,333 --> 00:47:31,333
And I'm married, and I'm never
gonna be alone again, right?

827
00:47:36,608 --> 00:47:41,608
