858
00:48:57,460 --> 00:49:00,180
- See, I don't know if
I'm gonna go for the Navy,

859
00:49:00,180 --> 00:49:02,020
the Marines, or the Merchant Marines,

860
00:49:02,020 --> 00:49:04,220
but God made the US
number one for a reason,

861
00:49:04,220 --> 00:49:05,800
and we gotta uphold that responsibility.

862
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:07,660
- Well what if bombs ever
fall on this country?

863
00:49:07,660 --> 00:49:10,880
I mean, what would happen to
us, what would be our fate?

864
00:49:12,050 --> 00:49:13,650
- Our fate?

865
00:49:13,650 --> 00:49:15,333
You use such weird words sometimes.

866
00:49:15,333 --> 00:49:16,635
(laughs)

867
00:49:16,635 --> 00:49:17,468
Don't worry about it.

868
00:49:17,468 --> 00:49:18,720
If the Japs try to bomb the US,

869
00:49:18,720 --> 00:49:19,990
we will blast them out of the sky

870
00:49:19,990 --> 00:49:22,420
with the secrete missiles
that we're making at Lockheed.

871
00:49:23,900 --> 00:49:26,670
You know, some of the women
whose husbands are overseas

872
00:49:26,670 --> 00:49:28,280
have started working for the war effort,

873
00:49:28,280 --> 00:49:29,250
and I was thinking that--

874
00:49:29,250 --> 00:49:31,320
- Glazer women don't
work outside of the home.

875
00:49:32,480 --> 00:49:34,250
- But it's war time, isn't that different?

876
00:49:34,250 --> 00:49:35,780
- No wife of mine, ever.

877
00:49:38,780 --> 00:49:39,990
- More macaroni and cheese?

878
00:49:39,990 --> 00:49:42,529
We have potatoes and biscuits,

879
00:49:42,529 --> 00:49:45,890
I got tapioca pudding with
bananas and whipped cream.

880
00:49:45,890 --> 00:49:47,210
You liked it, didn't you Daddy?

881
00:49:47,210 --> 00:49:49,240
I mean, I just wanna be the best wife

882
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,650
in the whole world, I do.

883
00:49:50,650 --> 00:49:53,550
- No, it was delicious,
it was really good.

884
00:49:53,550 --> 00:49:55,960
But you know how that
white food kinda bloats me.

885
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:58,110
- Oh, there was ketchup Daddy, that's red.

886
00:49:59,110 --> 00:50:01,040
Oh, look what I made for Arina.

887
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:03,820
I made it out of a sock
and some black felt,

888
00:50:03,820 --> 00:50:06,813
it's just like the one I got
for Christmas at the orphanage.

889
00:50:06,813 --> 00:50:08,230
It's cute, huh? (laughs)

890
00:50:08,230 --> 00:50:09,870
- You got nothing else to do around here

891
00:50:09,870 --> 00:50:12,460
except for tending somebody else's kid?

892
00:50:12,460 --> 00:50:15,020
- Well, I just feel sorry for them,

893
00:50:15,020 --> 00:50:17,870
I mean Harriet's husband
is missing in action--

894
00:50:17,870 --> 00:50:19,577
- Enough about Harriet.

895
00:50:19,577 --> 00:50:20,410
- What?

896
00:50:20,410 --> 00:50:22,446
- I got you, baby.
(Norma Jeane squeals)

897
00:50:22,446 --> 00:50:24,790
(laughing)

898
00:50:24,790 --> 00:50:26,460
- Oh, she loves it.

899
00:50:26,460 --> 00:50:28,180
See, I used little black buttons for eyes.

900
00:50:28,180 --> 00:50:31,410
Oh, Harriet, if I had a Arina, I would be

901
00:50:31,410 --> 00:50:34,010
the happiest girl in the whole world!

902
00:50:34,010 --> 00:50:34,843
I would!

903
00:50:38,504 --> 00:50:41,254
(men chattering)

904
00:50:44,630 --> 00:50:45,480
- Listen to this.

905
00:50:46,610 --> 00:50:48,340
When you read this, Big Daddy,

906
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:50,180
think of Baby Doll and the red hot loving

907
00:50:50,180 --> 00:50:52,479
she's gonna give you when
you come home tonight.

908
00:50:52,479 --> 00:50:54,190
(laughing)
- Big Daddy.

909
00:50:54,190 --> 00:50:55,830
- She's always leaving notes in my lunch.

910
00:50:55,830 --> 00:50:58,860
She cooks and cleans and
scrubs everything all day.

911
00:50:58,860 --> 00:51:01,010
She's so neat, and pretty.

912
00:51:01,010 --> 00:51:02,310
She even writes me poetry.

913
00:51:03,410 --> 00:51:05,060
- This is better than any poetry.

914
00:51:06,020 --> 00:51:07,020
Take a look at this.

915
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:09,113
My girl.

916
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:12,320
- Not as sexy as my Norma Jeane.

917
00:51:13,190 --> 00:51:15,349
I mean, if she had that kinda underwear.

918
00:51:15,349 --> 00:51:17,599
(laughing)

919
00:51:20,133 --> 00:51:21,693
(laughs)

920
00:51:21,693 --> 00:51:22,690
- All this makeup.

921
00:51:22,690 --> 00:51:24,450
- Oh, shh, come on, be a sport.

922
00:51:25,549 --> 00:51:28,540
I want the guys to see
how beautiful my wife is.

923
00:51:28,540 --> 00:51:29,640
Okay, smile for Daddy.

924
00:51:31,346 --> 00:51:33,930
Put your arm behind your head like this.

925
00:51:33,930 --> 00:51:35,920
See, that's what they call a glamour shot.

926
00:51:35,920 --> 00:51:37,744
You like to look glamorous, huh?

927
00:51:37,744 --> 00:51:39,214
(laughing)

928
00:51:39,214 --> 00:51:42,047
(camera clicking)

929
00:51:45,460 --> 00:51:47,740
- Daddy, come on, that's enough.

930
00:51:47,740 --> 00:51:50,200
It's lonely here in this
big old bed by myself.

931
00:51:51,503 --> 00:51:53,794
(camera clicking)

932
00:51:53,794 --> 00:51:54,842
- [Bucky] That's good now.

933
00:51:54,842 --> 00:51:58,730
- Daddy, I don't wanna,
it doesn't feel right,

934
00:51:58,730 --> 00:52:01,901
I mean, I just, this
wig, and this makeup, I--

935
00:52:01,901 --> 00:52:03,990
- No no, you likey, you likey, you like it

936
00:52:03,990 --> 00:52:05,871
because it makes me hot.

937
00:52:05,871 --> 00:52:07,890
Don't, it's fun, it's fun.

938
00:52:07,890 --> 00:52:10,680
- No, Bucky, no, see, it's not fun.

939
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:12,210
- Come on, would you loosen up?

940
00:52:12,210 --> 00:52:14,460
Guys do things like this with
their wives all the time.

941
00:52:14,460 --> 00:52:15,530
There's no harm in it.

942
00:52:15,530 --> 00:52:17,980
- I just, I don't like
looking like this, I mean,

943
00:52:19,491 --> 00:52:21,260
it makes me not know who I am.

944
00:52:22,184 --> 00:52:24,100
I thought you loved me.

945
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:27,580
- You know, sometimes I don't think

946
00:52:27,580 --> 00:52:29,100
you feel much in your body.

947
00:52:29,100 --> 00:52:29,933
- What?

948
00:52:29,933 --> 00:52:31,180
- The way a woman is supposed to feel.

949
00:52:31,180 --> 00:52:34,124
- No, Bucky, I didn't mean it, I'm just,

950
00:52:34,124 --> 00:52:38,670
I'm sorry, I'm getting my period
and I have terrible cramps,

951
00:52:38,670 --> 00:52:40,670
and I'll pose--
- Then take an aspirin.

952
00:52:43,030 --> 00:52:44,880
- No, Bucky, wait.

953
00:52:44,880 --> 00:52:47,199
- This is strictly confidential, okay?

954
00:52:47,199 --> 00:52:49,130
Not to go beyond us.

955
00:52:51,660 --> 00:52:52,660
- This is your wife?

956
00:52:53,554 --> 00:52:55,940
Glazer, you're one lucky bastard.

957
00:52:56,810 --> 00:52:58,540
- Man, if I had a wife
that looked like this,

958
00:52:58,540 --> 00:53:01,301
I wouldn't be showing
her pictures to nobody.

959
00:53:01,301 --> 00:53:03,020
I'd be putting her under lock and key.

960
00:53:03,020 --> 00:53:05,290
- Ah, well, I don't have
to worry about that.

961
00:53:06,338 --> 00:53:08,150
Norma Jeane's only got eyes for me.

962
00:53:10,578 --> 00:53:13,290
(knocking)

963
00:53:13,290 --> 00:53:14,123
- Harriet?

964
00:53:19,880 --> 00:53:21,180
- Harriet left last night.

965
00:53:22,300 --> 00:53:24,050
She packed up Arina and took off.

966
00:53:24,050 --> 00:53:26,150
She said she wasn't cut out to be a widow.

967
00:53:27,077 --> 00:53:28,721
(laughs)

968
00:53:28,721 --> 00:53:31,120
- She wouldn't leave
without saying goodbye,

969
00:53:31,120 --> 00:53:33,620
without having Arina say
goodbye, she wouldn't--

970
00:53:33,620 --> 00:53:35,080
- Well she would and she did.

971
00:53:35,080 --> 00:53:36,660
- She would not.

972
00:53:36,660 --> 00:53:38,120
God wouldn't let her.

973
00:53:42,399 --> 00:53:45,209
(insects chirping)

974
00:53:45,209 --> 00:53:47,792
(somber music)

975
00:53:58,575 --> 00:54:01,075
(baby crying)

976
00:54:14,266 --> 00:54:16,266
(gasps)

977
00:54:24,231 --> 00:54:25,398
- Norma Jeane?

978
00:54:34,539 --> 00:54:36,789
Norma Jeane, you mopped
this floor yesterday.

979
00:54:41,510 --> 00:54:42,343
Listen honey.

980
00:54:43,870 --> 00:54:46,110
I enlisted this morning
in the Merchant Marines.

981
00:54:48,300 --> 00:54:50,180
And we both knew that this was coming.

982
00:54:51,550 --> 00:54:53,400
Probably be shipped out in six weeks.

983
00:54:54,490 --> 00:54:55,790
I have to serve my country.

984
00:54:55,790 --> 00:54:57,740
May sound corny, but that's how I feel.

985
00:55:00,546 --> 00:55:01,463
- Oh Bucky.

986
00:55:03,381 --> 00:55:04,214
- Dear God.

987
00:55:06,010 --> 00:55:08,010
Help us mortals to understand your will.

988
00:55:11,450 --> 00:55:12,283
- [Norma Jeane] Daddy.

989
00:55:12,283 --> 00:55:14,420
- [Bucky] Norma Jeane, I told
you, I gotta get my sleep,

990
00:55:14,420 --> 00:55:16,260
I have to report early in the morning.

991
00:55:16,260 --> 00:55:17,710
- Gimme a baby.

992
00:55:17,710 --> 00:55:18,620
I want a baby.

993
00:55:18,620 --> 00:55:20,700
- I'll be damned, Norma
Jeane, we went through this.

994
00:55:20,700 --> 00:55:22,800
World War II is no time to start a family.

995
00:55:23,671 --> 00:55:25,770
- [Norma Jeane] Don't
leave me Daddy, please,

996
00:55:25,770 --> 00:55:27,220
if you leave me I'll die.

997
00:55:27,220 --> 00:55:29,090
- [Bucky] Calm down, you're not gonna die.

998
00:55:31,915 --> 00:55:33,670
- [Norma Jeane] I want a baby.

999
00:55:33,670 --> 00:55:34,980
- Norma Jeane.

1000
00:55:34,980 --> 00:55:36,090
Norma Jeane, stop it.

1001
00:55:36,090 --> 00:55:38,230
Just stop it, you're smothering me.

1002
00:55:38,230 --> 00:55:39,063
- Oh Daddy.

1003
00:55:39,063 --> 00:55:41,738
- Look, cooking and
cleaning and making out

1004
00:55:41,738 --> 00:55:44,940
like I'm God or something,
I don't wanna be God.

1005
00:55:44,940 --> 00:55:47,110
Just get off of me, you sad sick cow!

1006
00:55:51,765 --> 00:55:53,848
(crying)

1007
00:55:56,540 --> 00:55:59,514
Norma Jeane, what the hell?

1008
00:55:59,514 --> 00:56:01,940
- No.

1009
00:56:01,940 --> 00:56:03,340
Oh Daddy.

1010
00:56:03,340 --> 00:56:05,271
You love me, don't you?

1011
00:56:05,271 --> 00:56:06,104
Don't you Daddy?
- Sure I do.

1012
00:56:06,104 --> 00:56:07,330
Sure I love you, baby, come on.

1013
00:56:07,330 --> 00:56:08,790
I married you, didn't I?

1014
00:56:08,790 --> 00:56:10,143
- I love you.

1015
00:56:10,143 --> 00:56:11,093
I love you so much.

1016
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:13,632
Don't leave me.

1017
00:56:13,632 --> 00:56:16,022
(crying)

1018
00:56:16,022 --> 00:56:18,605
(somber music)

1019
00:56:26,542 --> 00:56:28,980
- Goodbye Norma Jeane.

1020
00:56:28,980 --> 00:56:31,970
She was a sweet kid, but so emotional.

1021
00:56:31,970 --> 00:56:34,370
She was wanting love all the time.

1022
00:56:34,370 --> 00:56:36,460
She was immature and unreliable.

1023
00:56:38,070 --> 00:56:40,750
But I guess so was I.

1024
00:56:40,750 --> 00:56:41,650
We were too young.

1025
00:56:42,720 --> 00:56:43,870
If she would've been a better cook

1026
00:56:43,870 --> 00:56:46,720
and not so emotional, it might've worked.

1027
00:56:46,720 --> 00:56:49,150
- If he loved me, he
wouldn't have left me.

1028
00:56:50,160 --> 00:56:51,810
If he left me, he didn't love me.

1029
00:56:52,957 --> 00:56:57,230
I was 18, no longer a ward of LA County,

1030
00:56:57,230 --> 00:57:00,490
for the first time in my life, I was free.

1031
00:57:02,190 --> 00:57:04,510
Not an orphan or a foster child,

1032
00:57:04,510 --> 00:57:06,910
not a daughter or a
daughter-in-law, not a wife.

1033
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:09,580
Because of the war, I was free.

1034
00:57:11,790 --> 00:57:13,763
My life would now begin.

1035
00:57:16,057 --> 00:57:21,057
I was nobody's daughter.

1036
00:57:22,370 --> 00:57:25,370
(upbeat jazz music)

1037
00:57:30,460 --> 00:57:31,920
- Norma Jeane.

1038
00:57:31,920 --> 00:57:34,340
This stuff'll penetrate your brain.

1039
00:57:34,340 --> 00:57:35,910
Maybe you better get some fresh air.

1040
00:57:35,910 --> 00:57:37,200
- I don't get tired.

1041
00:57:37,200 --> 00:57:41,597
I mean, I don't have time, I
wouldn't want to lose my job.

1042
00:57:41,597 --> 00:57:44,042
(laughing)

1043
00:57:44,042 --> 00:57:45,740
Sorry, I'm just a little dizzy.

1044
00:57:46,970 --> 00:57:48,060
Gosh. (laughs)

1045
00:57:48,060 --> 00:57:49,740
- I notice your wedding rings.

1046
00:57:50,650 --> 00:57:54,240
- Oh, yeah, my husband's
lost in action in New Guinea.

1047
00:57:54,240 --> 00:57:55,460
- I'm sorry.

1048
00:57:55,460 --> 00:57:56,293
Must be lonely.

1049
00:57:57,340 --> 00:57:58,930
You live alone?

1050
00:57:58,930 --> 00:58:01,370
- Oh, a furnished room in
Burbank, but I love it.

1051
00:58:01,370 --> 00:58:03,470
Not so much housework for just one person.

1052
00:58:04,458 --> 00:58:06,680
- Maybe some night we could have dinner.

1053
00:58:08,270 --> 00:58:11,042
- Oh, well, I wouldn't feel right

1054
00:58:11,042 --> 00:58:14,589
until I know where my husband is.

1055
00:58:14,589 --> 00:58:16,672
(laughs)

1056
00:58:31,970 --> 00:58:33,015
- Hold it.

1057
00:58:33,015 --> 00:58:34,880
(camera clicks)

1058
00:58:34,880 --> 00:58:36,050
Beautiful.

1059
00:58:36,050 --> 00:58:38,490
- Oh no, I can't, please, I can't.

1060
00:58:38,490 --> 00:58:40,890
- Come on, it's for the boys overseas,

1061
00:58:40,890 --> 00:58:42,490
the stars and stripes.

